description: Drifting in space, the Bea Arthur has been damaged almost beyond repair by a sudden attack. There is only enough life support for two people, so Deadpool must choose which of his teammates to release from cryo-sleep in order to save the rest. Please, please, PLEASE don't let it be Dogpool!
name: You Say You Want Revolution (Part 1)

name: Dance-Hall Racket

description: This book contains newspaper strip reprints from 12/21/41 through 3/10/42. It finishes up "The Mole" story arc, includes the complete "Jacques the Blackmailer" story arc, and begins the B.B. Eyes story arc.

Kyo Aizawa is very excited about getting to attend Seisyu Academy, which is famous for its adorable girls' uniforms. Her spirits are crushed, however, when she opens the package containing her school uniform to find a boy's uniform. Her father explains to her that, as Seisyu Academy is also famous for its boys' basketball program, he enrolled her as a boy so she can fulfill his own dream of becoming an NBA basketball star. To make matters worse, she has to stay in the boys' dorms, and her roommate is the same boy she came to hate at tryouts.
name: Vol. 1

description: Just when Chiharu has decided he doesn't hate Kyo all that much and they can be friends, he accidentally touches her breast. Kyo, afraid she might be found out, makes a hurried excuse and comes up with a plan to make herself seem more masculine. Also in this volume: 'Change' and 'Uso Tsuki na Kanojo' (False Girlfriend) - two one-off stories.
name: Vol. 2

description: Enter Tsuyaka Himejima. A recent transfer to Kyo's new high school, she is very disappointed to discover her former teammate's gender-bending masquerade, and comes up with a plan to get Kyo onto the girls basketball team by hook or by crook!
name: Vol. 3

description: When Chiharu discovers Kyo's true gender, he shows her the door and tells her that he can't be her roommate anymore. Devastated, and with nowhere to go, Kyo moves into a cardboard box in the park, where her hoop dreams begin to turn into overtime nightmares!
name: Vol. 4

description: When Kensuke Yura, the boy who puts himself ahead of the team, worms his way back to boys' basketball squad, not everyone is giving him high-fives. Kyo feels sorry for him, and wants to be a good teammate by being his friend. Will Kensuke take advantage of her assist? Or will he just foul out?
name: Vol. 5

description: Kensuke is still wary of Kyo's friendship, but Kyo is willing to prove herself and take one for team. But just as Kensuke warms up to her, he overhears a conversation that makes him want a replay. Will their friendship permanently foul out?
name: Vol. 6

description: They're back at it! Now that everyone has recovered from Kensuke's foul play, Chiharu and Kyo are teaming up and living together again...and things couldn't be any worse. Chiharu tells Kyo what he really thinks of her--and she decides that she must re-introduce him to her feminine side!
name: Vol. 7

description: The perfect combination for love: magical mushrooms and steamy hot springs! Imai decides that the basketball team should go on a mushroom gathering trip to the hot springs. During the trip Kensuke tells an annoyed Chiharu that he's asked Kyo to go steady with him. To spice things up, Kyo and Chiharu mistakenly eat some mushrooms, which make them behave in rather uncharacteristic ways - like confessing their love for each other! Is it love brewing or are the mushrooms doing the talking?
name: Vol. 8

description: Hamaya's plan to kidnap Chiharu's "sister" Kyoko, who is really just Kyo dressed all girly, is rejected by Imai and Tsuyaka's double team. While the dynamic duo answer Chiharu's call to save them from Hamaya, Tsuyaka isn't fazed by the fake out and soon realizes that Kyoko is Kyo in disguise. She decides to give Kyo an assist and helps her make the prefect fade away...locking lips with Chiharu.
name: Vol. 9

description: Kyo's secret has been revealed to the entire basketball team, and now she has made a deal to defeat the whole team single-handedly or leave forever. She has made it past every member of the team except the captain, Hisashi Imai. Now she'll have to pull out all her tricks and play some real basketball.
name: Vol. 10

description: Did you know that Sidekick City and Riverdale share the same downtown area? Did you know they also share the same school buses, playgrounds and dry cleaners? Well, the Tiny Titans and Little Archie's gang didn't know, either! What would happen if suddenly their two worlds collided? Would Archie and his pals start wearing costumes? Would the Titans start wearing sweater sets? Talk about your crossover crisis! Join us for this historical event, as two of the most awesome 2-D teams ever meet for the first time! Aw yeah, Archie Titans!
name: Malfunctioning; Ketchup: Be Mine; Buzzin

description: What kind of hell is coming for Asgard? What does Asgard’s presence on earth mean? Only one man knows for sure and he can’t get anyone to take him seriously. The reconstruction of his fallen city are first and foremost in the God of Thunder’s mind as an evil more terrifying than even he could imagine comes roaring down the World Tree. The Dark Gods are coming for Asgard. Here is blood! Here is thunder! HERE IS THE MIGHTY THOR!

Bogey man appears with Satanas, The Wizard and his apprentice in the Cap Milksop-story.

Satanas also has his own story.
Captain Milksop only appears on the cover.

description: After an increase of demon activity on Earth, Pandora travels to Hell to stop it. But what she discovers there, is much worse!

In Hell, Pandora meets Maelstrom, a demoness given a special armor specifically designed to use against Pandora. On Earth, Anna Martelli must make a difficult decision: battling the forces of Hell alone, or ask an enemy to help her for a prize.

The fight for the Demonography! Can Strife's demons be trusted or will they make their own plans? Who will end up with the book of spells and what has Pandora seen in the book that scared her so much?

This Gothic shojo manga is a single volume comprising three stories--a main one, "One with the Glass Wings," and two shorter stories "Firefly" and "Jion Princess"--that feature characters falling in and out of love, against all odds. There is a fragility to the main characters in each story; each is afflicted with some sort of physical and/or mental ailment--for instance, a blood disease is the affliction in the main story. But regardless of all the obstacles and interference, love conquers all.

Contents

  • GLASS WINGS Episode 1
  • GLASS WINGS Episode 2
  • GLASS WINGS Final Episode
  • FIREFLY
  • JOIN PRINCESS
  • POSTSCRIPT
name: Vol. 1

description:
Her name's Grace. She's been sick for as long as she can remember, and lies in bed all day. Her family's wealthy, so she has all the comforts in the world...except for love. Her father's a drunk, and her mother's dead.

But when a mysterious young man appears at Grace's balcony, everything changes. The boy challenges Grace to leave her room, despite her condition. Eventually she does...and, strangely, she doesn't feel sick anymore. Because the world outside is nothing like what she imagined it to be...
name: Vol. 1

description: Shi-Hyun is a girl who has nothing but bad luck--at least that's what everyone believes, and in some ways, Shi-Hyun herself believes this, too, forcing her to stay away from people. As a result, she has developed an outer shell, making her look tough and indifferent even with the constantly bullying. When she transfers to a different high school, a fresh start brings an array of new characters into her life: Queen Bee has a cool personality and the fighting skills to match, making her one of the most popular girls in school. And the irresistibly charming Cold Prince Ma-Hyun has the good looks to make the girls swoon. Finally, the new girl Hee-Soo doesn't seem to mind getting close to Shi-Hyun--but Hee-Soo has an agenda of her own...
name: Vol. 1

description: Pandora is trying to get to the legendary Gundevil by posing as an arms buyer. She let him slip through her fingers in the early 70's. Will she be able to catch him now?

Shi-Hyun's new "friend," Hee-Soo, is secretly plotting revenge against her in the name of family. And Shi-Hyun is walking right into her trap... But that's only the beginning! Still ahead are confessions of love, acts of jealousy, and an unforgettable fit of rage. Will Shi-Hyun come to terms with her feelings for her stepbrother? Will Ma-Hyun convince her to date him instead? If hatred doesn't break Shi-Hyun's spirits, perhaps love will!
name: Vol. 2

description: Da-Min invites Shi-Hyun to the television station with him, where it seems that more than a few people have taken interest in her. Will Shi-Hyun fall hard after getting caught up in a celebrity whirlwind? The flash of a photo shoot, an extreme makeover, and secret love interests--it's all inside this next volume of Good Luck!
name: Vol. 3

description: Ma-Hyun accidentally finds out that Shi-Hyun's new friend is none other than his friend Da-Min! Will these two friends become sworn enemies as they vie for Shi-Hyun's love? And when a new girl, So-Youn, arrives on the scene, Shi-Hyun discovers that she's just as susceptible to jealousy. Whom does Shi-Hyun really love, and what does he know that she doesn't?
name: Vol. 4

description: The final volume! Shi-Hyun starts to feel like she has to compete for Ma-Hyun's love with the girl she used to be before she lost her memory--a competition that's rigged from the start! And Shi-Woo, seeing the pain Ma-Hyun is causing Shi-Hyun, decides it's time to stop pretending to be her brother and deal with Ma-Hyun once and for all. When everything comes crashing down, will Shi-Hyun be any closer to the truth about her amnesia--and her extraordinary bad luck?
name: Vol. 5

description: Pandora tells Anna of her first encounter with Strife, about 3000 years ago. In modern day, Strife is resurrected in Mirida, Mexico.
Pandora is able to defeat the Gundevil and sent him back to her fabled chest. But who is the figure lurking near the chest?
Pandora can't escape Hell alone. She must enlist the aid of Maelstrom. But will Maelstrom agree to help the enemy she was created to defeat?

Firiel is a fifteen-year-old girl who lives with her father, the astronomer Professor Dee, and their servants, the Holys. When she is invited to a fancy ball at a count’s castle, she discovers that her past is more complicated then she had thought. A necklace given to her by her father proves that she is of royal blood--and a candidate to be the next Queen!
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: The Good Witch of the West

description: Narrowly escaping the destruction of her home, Firiel escapes to the Count's castle, where she begs Adale and Eusis to help her find Rune. When they track him down at the Star Queen's estate, Firiel and Adale hatch a plan to save Firiel's friend themselves, and the two go in fully disguised. But when they stumble upon the black-cloaked men who destroyed Firiel's home, the rescue turns into a fight for survival!
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: The Good Witch of the West

description: Firiel soon learns the price of her bargain with the Count of Rualgo. At Taurus Academy, the girls treat her lower than a dog. She's willing to take the abuse for the sake of Rune's protection by the Count. But will her questionable friendship with her fencing instructor scar Rune even more?
name: Vol. 3

volume.name: The Good Witch of the West

description: The charade is up at Taurus Academy and Firiel must return to the Roland estate. She will finally be face-to-face with the other Queen-in-waiting, Leandra. In this game of chess, two Queens must make power moves in order to rule the land. With Rune by her side, Firiel is destined to be the queen.
name: Vol. 4

volume.name: The Good Witch of the West

description: While two intelligent and ambitious Queens-in-Waiting duel for succession to Graal's throne, a greater challenge awaits our plucky heroine Firiel in the south--where dragons and unicorns roam, and even the best intentions of friends may twist into poisonous lies...
name: Vol. 5

volume.name: The Good Witch of the West

description: In an uncharacteristic display of clumsiness, our brash heroine Firiel manages to fall through the Wall, the massive dragon-impeding barrier at the end of the world. Magically transported thousands of miles away to the land of Brigion, Firiel stumbles upon a restless army that will storm through Graal--unless Firiel can warn them first!
name: Vol. 6

volume.name: The Good Witch of the West

description:
Welcome to turn-of-the-century Paris! Ball gowns swirl, champagne corks pop, and precious jewels sparkle all around the city--and in the amethyst eyes of one particular young man... Meet Florian, the only son of an impoverished noble family. When his family's 120-carat Flame of Mughal goes missing, Florian teams up with the stunning, mysterious Ray Balzac Courland to track down the dazzling gem. But the trail of clues leads the duo to an abandoned castle--and a deadly secret! A boys' love action-romance set on magnificent streets of gay Paree, Gorgeous Carat follows the swashbuckling adventures of Ray and Florian as they battle crime lords, backstabbing family members, and a possible attraction to each other.

Contents

  • First Curtain: The Flame of Mughal
  • Second Curtain: The Circumstances of Petit Noel
name: Vol. 1

description: When Florian is taken hostage by the evil Black Hand organization, will Phantom Thief Noir come to the rescue...or will he keep the precious jewels for himself? And what adventures await as the gang heads down to Morocco to meet Ray's old friend? Things heat up in book two of Gorgeous Carat as Ray and Florian seek out the ancient treasure of the Knights Templar!
name: Vol. 2

description: Our story continues with Noir being tortured by Azura who threatens to harm his followers if Noir doesn't agree to help him with the mystery of the Knights Templar. In the meantime, Solomon Sugar searches for the boss of the Black Hand to exact his revenge. Meanwhile, Florian is recovering from his opium addiction. What else can happen to them?
name: Vol. 3

description: The sadness continues between Noir and Florian. The promise land that they both dream about is not becoming a reality. Azura's only goal in life is to make Noir suffer. Noir is ready to endure anything that Azura can throw at him. Is Noir ready to lose Florian forever to Azura?
name: Vol. 4

description:
"ANGEL Corps" is a 32 page Full Color Standard Sized Comic Book. 
 
Eric Linquist's first story picks up a time in the Earth's near future where a select number of humans develop rudimentary, low-level super-powers that don't work all the time but soon begin to work enough to cause some unwanted damage across the planet. The media dubs these individuals "megahumans." Concerned nations agree to send them all to a super-funded U.N. for sophisticated analysis into the phenomena.  As megahumans around the world decide to journey to New York City, their powers begin to amplify into supercharged high gear just as a planet threatening crisis erupts. Can seven of them who step up form an alliance of nations, a team of angels, charged with guarding Earth from the deadliest newly-emergent planetary threats?  

Eric's second story unfolds in ancient Atlantis, where we are introduced to an elite team of warrior angels that have become inexplicably separated from their god, the Omniety and have split up into two factions. Angel Dommine' leads the group that wants to guide humans directly while Angel Destine' leads those who believe in a non-interference directive, assisting only from afar. Their conflict escalates into calamitous destruction and gets them all hurled into a timeless dimension for over 1,000 years!  Present-day mankind inadvertently frees them from their dormant state, releasing the angels into our present day, godless, feuding and coping with an era they've never could have imagined!

What will happen when  ANGEL Corps is called upon to go up against elite warrior angels?
name: "Orientation"

description:
"ANGEL Corps" is a 32 page Full Color Standard Sized Comic Book.    
 
Issue 2 opens with the world’s first superpowered being, I-Force, crashing up and out of a UN orientation of global megahumans. Touted as a fire drill, five in the assembly realize it is anything but - and they avoid security to follow I-Force into the stratosphere, soon coming to realize they are face to face with huge asteroid fragments heading straight for New York City. How did Earth’s advanced tracking equipment miss these huge harbingers of destruction? What can five inexperienced megahumans do to help I-Force save the city?

Meanwhile, in the parallel storyline, two split factions of elite warrior angels duke it out in downtown Atlantis unleashing powerful angelic forces. Fearing ultimate destruction, an Antlantean leader unleashes modified angel technology to get them to stop, but will he be in time?   History holds the clues!
name: "Lessen One"

description:
"She first caught my eye...when I saw her white wrist...peeking out from the edge of darkness. It was pale as porcelain...and the mark loomed out from it." Before they were friends, he had already noticed her. He wanted her hands--those beautiful, enchanting hands--to himself. And he hoped that the local madman who had been "collecting" the hands of anything that moved--babies, children, men, women, animals--would get them for him...until the day she asked him to teach her how to smile. In four gruesome stories, two murder-fixated teens lose themselves in their obsession. But can you handle seeing humanity's darkest side revealed in all its glaring, gory glory?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter I: Wrist-cut
  • Chapter II: Goth
  • Chapter III: Grave
  • Chapter IV: Twins
  • Chapter V: Twins II

Everything from the first appearance of Deadman to a team-up between he and Hawkman can be found here!

Fortunately there’s a summer in between and she decides this is the best time to let down her hair and get wild. The star-studded Avengers anthology continues as Greg Rucka makes his return to mighty Marvel with a tale of the star-spangled Avenger Steve Rogers!

Honoring the fallen of the Siege of Asgard, the former Captain America will never let them be forgotten! When two separate nights out on the town result in ex-Avengers (and ex-soulmates) Firestar and Justice bumping into each other, the truly unexpected happens!

Plus, with so many different (and hungry!) Avengers converging in New York, what's on the day's menu for Jarvis?
